comments.body:
I do prefer the current order here because I find it more intuitive to have the input first and then the output. But I think in `GetCommandFromShortCommandID` the input (`shortID`) should be `const` and casing should be fixed to `short_id`. nit: Overall I would prefer a more consistent API between the two functions so that they have the same return type:

```suggestion
// returns the short command ID for a command (string)
// returns 0 if short command ID was not found
bool GetShortCommandIDFromCommand(const std::string& cmd, uint8_t short_id);

// returns the command (string) from a short command ID
// returns an empty string if short command ID has not been found
bool GetCommandFromShortCommandID(const uint8_t short_id, std::string& cmd);
```

